  {
    "model": "pages.post",
    "pk": 3,
    "fields": {
      "title": "Building Automated Finance Tools with Python",
      "category": "Python / Data Science",
      "date": "2026-04-12",
      "image": "blog/python_logo.jpg",
      "content": "Managing finances in Nigeria can be complex with inflation and multiple income streams. Thats why I decided to build Budget-Pilot, a personal expense tracker.\r\n\r\nThe Process ;\r\n\r\nUsing Python and MySQL, I developed a system that:\r\n\r\nTracks every Naira spent in real-time.\r\n\r\nCategorizes expenses automatically.\r\n\r\nVisualizes monthly spending trends.\r\n\r\nThe Lesson ;\r\n\r\nThe biggest challenge wasn't the code; it was the data structure. Moving from a beginner to an intermediate Python developer meant learning how to handle database relations efficiently"
    }
  },
